Thus, \(|A \cap B| = 2 \times 22!\). 5. **Applying Inclusion-Exclusion**: - \(|A \cup B| = |A| + |B| - |A \cap B| = 2 \times 23! + 2 \times 23! - 2 \times 22!\) - Simplifying, we get \(|A \cup B| = 4 \times 23! - 2 \times 22! = 2 \times 22!(4 \times 2 - 1) = 2 \times 22! \times 3 = 6 \times 22!\). 6. **Probability Calculation**: - The number of permutations where Charlie is adjacent to at least one of Chris or Abby is \(6 \times 22!\). - The probability is \(\frac{6 \times 22!}{25!} = \frac{6}{25 \times 24} = \frac{6}{600} = \frac{1}{100}\).
